            <abstract id="ref4" label="Abstract">These are Hopi and Tewa Indian recording transcriptions, but primarily Hopi. There are eighteen Indian informants who provide information on names of plants, birds, reptiles, and other animals, including domesticated; costumes, including Kachina; migration legend; place-names; kinship terms; numerals; weaving; pottery; Hopi, Huichol and Tarahumara belts; medicine men; etc.</abstract>
